1
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:15,933
<i> I can't remember so much.</i>

2
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,133
<i> We must be close.</i>

3
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,033
<i> Of course.</i>

4
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,833
<i> We're best friends.</i>

5
00:00:20,967 --> 00:00:24,067
<i> I forgot to take my medicine.</i>

6
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,300
<i>Friend, can you pass it to me?
It's over there...</i>

7
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:29,633
<i> I'll take her to the hospital.</i>

8
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:30,967
<i> But let her suffer for now.</i>

9
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:33,200
<i> Doctor, who brought her here?</i>

10
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,967
<i> We just want to thank them.</i>

11
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:35,967
<i> I did.</i>

12
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:37,333
<i>So mom really was with you
all along!</i>

13
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> Why did you kidnap her?</i>

14
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,433
<i>Hazel! What kind of nonsense
is this?</i>

15
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:42,700
<i> Instead of thanking me,</i>

16
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,033
<i> you're angry?</i>

17
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,933
<i> I saved Felma's life.</i>

18
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:48,200
<i> We're just wondering...</i>

19
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:50,000
<i> why did you come to Hazel?</i>

20
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,533
<i> Because...</i>

21
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:53,367
<i> she's my best friend.</i>

22
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:56,100
<i> I owe her my life.</i>

23
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,667
This is so annoying, Alice!

24
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,867
Nothing went the way
I thought it would.

25
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,400
It's the opposite!

26
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:05,467
You know,

27
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,600
Manuel's illegitimate children
even accused me

28
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,200
of kidnapping Felma.

29
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:12,067
Nothing went the way I expected.

30
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:15,233
I thought I'd look
like a hero to Manuel.

31
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,467
Relax, okay? Just calm down!

32
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:23,633
I have to go on duty now.

33
00:01:23,767 --> 00:01:24,700
What?

34
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:27,333
Where are you going?
You're acting so strange.

35
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:32,067
What?

36
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:34,367
What now, Manuel?

37
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,033
What are you accusing me of
this time?

38
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:37,333
Aren't you done yet?

39
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:40,100
Felma's looking for you.

40
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,833
She told me what happened.

41
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:47,467
Thank you
for taking care of her.

42
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,100
I told you, didn't I?

43
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,100
But you wouldn't listen...

44
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,300
until Felma said it.

45
00:01:58,233 --> 00:02:02,000
I hope next time, Manuel,

46
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:04,333
other people don't matter
whether they see me

47
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:06,767
do good things.

48
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,800
I hope...

49
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:11,667
it'll be your eyes that notice.

50
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:21,167
The swelling has increased,
and the tumor is growing fast.

51
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:25,767
It might affect
Miss Felma's memory loss.

52
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,900
And we don't know
if it's cancerous.

53
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:30,767
We need to remove it
as soon as possible.

54
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:33,967
We can do the procedure here
at Southcrest Premier

55
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:37,933
or in Davao with Dr. Yunque,
if you're more comfortable.

56
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,033
No.

57
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:41,667
She might not wake up
after the surgery.

58
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:45,533
We need to go through
with the operation.

59
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,400
Can't you see what's happening?
It's just getting worse.

60
00:02:48,767 --> 00:02:51,000
Mom barely
remembers anything.

61
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:54,000
Her headaches are getting worse,
and now she's having seizures.

62
00:02:55,933 --> 00:02:59,500
Can you stop being scared?
Mom will wake up.

63
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:02,300
What if she wakes up,

64
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:04,133
but it gets worse?

65
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:06,000
Why are you two so negative?

66
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:08,967
Kids, calm down.

67
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:11,633
Let your mom decide.

68
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,867
The decision should be
from all of us.

69
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:17,767
We also need to make a decision
as a family.

70
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,167
What about you?

71
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:22,533
If it were up to me,
I'd say yes.

72
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,000
I believe your mom can get
better.

73
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:26,700
I don't want to.

74
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,300
Brain surgery is dangerous.

75
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:30,700
Please...

76
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,833
Can you just stop?

77
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:35,400
I don't want to pressure you,

78
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:37,633
but you need to make a decision.

79
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:40,300
Every hour counts.

80
00:03:41,667 --> 00:03:43,400
Excuse me.

81
00:03:46,167 --> 00:03:47,467
Friend?

82
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,433
Friend.

83
00:03:51,567 --> 00:03:53,367
If I may suggest,

84
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:56,967
you should get the surgery.

85
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,833
Didn't I promise you

86
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:02,900
when we were at my house?

87
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,333
I'll take care of you.

88
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:10,900
<i> Go on, Felma.</i>

89
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:13,067
<i> Get the surgery.</i>

90
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:16,633
<i> I just hope you don't wake up.</i>

91
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,133
<i> But if you do,</i>

92
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:22,567
<i>I'll be there
to take care of you.</i>

93
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:25,200
<i> But I'll steal your family.</i>

94
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:38,300
Friend,

95
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:40,433
I'm leaving for now, okay?

96
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:41,667
Please...

97
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:47,100
consider getting the surgery

98
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:48,533
before it's too late.

99
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,467
I'll be here.

100
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:56,000
As I said,

101
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,100
after the surgery,

102
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:02,267
I'll take care of you.

103
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,267
I'll be your personal nurse.

104
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,467
Thank you, Friend.

105
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,967
You're really kind.

106
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,067
Come visit again, okay?

107
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,433
Yes.

108
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:16,867
Yes, Felma.

109
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,833
<i> Why?</i>

110
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,567
Wait, what's going on?

111
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:39,233
Let go of me!

112
00:05:39,367 --> 00:05:41,233
What's your problem?

113
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:44,000
Why are you suddenly
so concerned about Felma?

114
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,033
And why does she think of you
as her best friend?

115
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:50,433
Did you give her something
to drink?

116
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:51,800
Did you, Hazel?

117
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:53,967
What do you think of me?
A fake doctor?

118
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,900
I'm a nurse!

119
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,533
Don't make me
look like an idiot.

120
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:02,933
What are you planning to do
to Felma?

121
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:04,767
I'm not making you look dumb.

122
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:06,667
You're just dumb.

123
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,067
You were together in Davao,

124
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:10,300
and nothing happened
between you?

125
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:14,367
That was your chance
to get the girl.

126
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,133
Get her?

127
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:18,033
Or steal her?

128
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:20,033
- Whatever.
- Just like what you did

129
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:21,367
to Manuel?

130
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,833
You know, get her,
steal her, it's the same.

131
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:27,133
The point is, you should've
been with Felma by now.

132
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,600
So that Manuel and I
would be together.

133
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:31,700
But you wasted
your opportunities.

134
00:06:33,067 --> 00:06:34,833
By "opportunity,"

135
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:38,233
you mean when you offered me
to team up with you?

136
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,567
To get Felma for myself?

137
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:43,000
Yes.

138
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:48,500
No, Hazel.

139
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:52,367
Even if you keep trying,

140
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,233
I won't team up with you.

141
00:06:55,367 --> 00:06:57,733
I'm not like you, Hazel.

142
00:06:57,867 --> 00:07:00,600
I won't force Felma to love me.

143
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:05,600
Because I know no one can
replace Manuel in her heart.

144
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:09,267
I admit there were times
I wished

145
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,400
Manuel's family were mine.

146
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:13,733
But I can't.

147
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,933
Because Felma doesn't love me.

148
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,633
And I respect that.

149
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:21,800
You're not just dumb,

150
00:07:21,933 --> 00:07:23,667
you're also a martyr.

151
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,467
No, Hazel.

152
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,100
I just know what love means.

153
00:07:28,233 --> 00:07:30,867
And it's not destructive.

154
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,033
It's not selfish.

155
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,833
It doesn't ruin lives.

156
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:40,000
Hazel, I know right from wrong.

157
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:41,333
The right thing...

158
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:43,500
is to let them be a family.

159
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:47,367
- And the wrong?
- What you're doing.

160
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,233
You're stopping them, Hazel.

161
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:52,700
Let Manuel go.

162
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:55,133
Let him be happy with Felma.

163
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,233
And accept the truth.

164
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:02,200
Manuel will never,
ever love you back.

165
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:05,700
How dare you!

166
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,467
You have no shame!

167
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,633
- You're rude!
- Rude?

168
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:22,100
I'm just giving you back
what you did, Hazel.

169
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:23,867
And don't lump me in

170
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:28,367
with people who tolerate
all your cruelty.

171
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:31,700
I don't have the patience
for people like you.

172
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,467
You want rude?

173
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,800
Fine.

174
00:08:34,933 --> 00:08:37,700
Try me. You're the one
who'll get hurt.

175
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,067
Noah, that's enough.

176
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,700
Bro.

177
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,500
Just let it go.

178
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,133
Thanks, Manuel.

179
00:08:57,167 --> 00:09:00,167
Hazel, I appreciate
that you helped Felma.

180
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,867
But this has to stop here.

181
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,967
Don't go near her anymore.

182
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:08,500
But she thinks of me
as her best friend.

183
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:12,567
And with her condition,

184
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,500
she needs me
to take care of her.

185
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:15,967
Hazel,

186
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:19,433
my kids and I are the ones
Felma needs. Not you.

187
00:09:19,567 --> 00:09:22,333
We can take care of her.
I can take care of her.

188
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:24,533
Manuel, wait. Don't do this.

189
00:09:25,767 --> 00:09:27,367
Felma needs me.

190
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,667
I'll take care of her.

191
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:30,833
Let me make it up to her.

192
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:35,200
Please, if you don't trust me
then just watch.

193
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,933
Stay there
while I take care of her.

194
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:38,333
Just, please.

195
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:41,200
Let me make things
right with Felma.

196
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:42,967
Please, Manuel.

197
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:45,500
Hazel, after everything
you've done to us,

198
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,667
how do you expect me
to trust you?

199
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,533
Dr. Emil Yunque,

200
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:59,900
my cousin, whom we asked
for a second opinion in Davao,

201
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,367
he says...

202
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:06,000
we should go through
with the operation.

203
00:10:15,567 --> 00:10:18,400
<i>I won't force Felma to love me.</i>

204
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:23,000
<i>I know no one can ever replace
Manuel in her heart.</i>

205
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,433
Manuel...

206
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:38,600
Felma. The kids and I will
just grab dinner, okay?

207
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:41,667
Go, Manuel.
I'll stay and watch over her.

208
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,700
I'll head out too, Felma.

209
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:48,433
Bye.

210
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:50,967
Bro, you haven't eaten yet,
right?

211
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:53,100
Why don't you come with us?

212
00:10:53,233 --> 00:10:55,100
- Come on.
- Well, I'll eat with them.

213
00:10:55,233 --> 00:10:56,233
Sure.

214
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,133
- All right. Thanks.
- I've got it, Bro. There.

215
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,567
This is so frustrating, Alice.

216
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,633
What I did didn't work.

217
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:11,933
Manuel thanked me, sure.

218
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:14,900
But he also told me
to stay away from Felma.

219
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:18,267
What did you expect?
You're their enemy.

220
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,733
There's still a silver lining.

221
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:22,500
Have you forgotten?

222
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:25,100
Felma now sees me
as her best friend.

223
00:11:26,433 --> 00:11:28,767
I'll use that to my advantage.

224
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:32,900
I'll use it to get into
Manuel and the kids' life.

225
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:35,333
So you're really going
to force this?

226
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:36,433
Of course.

227
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:40,067
You know,

228
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,567
I just need to convince Felma

229
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:44,800
that I should be the one
to take care of her.

230
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:46,500
Because once she wants it,

231
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:49,100
her children
won't have a choice.

232
00:11:49,233 --> 00:11:51,167
They can't go against her.

233
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:55,033
And most of all,
they can't stress Felma out.

234
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:04,933
You know, Sis, I thank the Lord
that you didn't forget me.

235
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:12,133
I don't remember much about you.

236
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:17,567
But even if I don't remember
much,

237
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:23,300
I can feel
that you're part of my life.

238
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:27,400
This illness is so hard.

239
00:12:29,767 --> 00:12:31,567
It's like...

240
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:35,367
I feel empty or something.

241
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:42,333
Like I don't have control
over my own thoughts.

242
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:50,700
Or maybe it's because I want to
remember what I lost so badly?

243
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:54,533
Maybe that's why.
That could be it.

244
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:58,400
Sis, don't force yourself
for now, okay?

245
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:02,833
But I'm just curious.

246
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:06,233
What does it feel like?

247
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:08,200
It's heavy.

248
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:12,033
Like I remember so many
things...

249
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,000
but only up to here.

250
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:19,267
They're running through my mind,

251
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:25,200
but I can't explain them.

252
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,500
Because it's...

253
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,500
foggy?

254
00:13:32,567 --> 00:13:35,400
Confusing. Blurry.

255
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,600
Like Hazel.

256
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:44,967
When I saw her,
I couldn't remember her.

257
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,300
Just like you.

258
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:55,200
But I can feel
she's also part of my life.

259
00:13:55,800 --> 00:14:00,267
<i>Felma's tumor
is destiny's gift to me.</i>

260
00:14:01,533 --> 00:14:05,400
Who would've thought Felma
would be my way

261
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:08,567
into Manuel's life
and his children's?

262
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:15,200
Felma's days are numbered.

263
00:14:16,867 --> 00:14:23,000
So I really need to step up,
I need better acting.

264
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:24,167
I'm so excited.

265
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:26,133
What should I wear
to Felma's wake?

266
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:27,200
What should I shop for?

267
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:28,467
What dress should I...

268
00:14:28,633 --> 00:14:30,800
I don't know. I'm just excited.

269
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:32,900
Wait...

270
00:14:33,033 --> 00:14:35,700
Are you seriously wishing
for Felma to die?

271
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:41,667
Alice, whether I wish it or not,
it's going to happen.

272
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,633
And you know what?

273
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:46,300
I feel like this tumor

274
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:49,133
will finally end the war
between Felma and me.

275
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:55,667
The doctor told us
not to tell you anything

276
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,800
that might stress you out.

277
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:05,167
But, Sis, there's something
I need to tell you.

278
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,200
About Hazel.

279
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:12,100
What are you saying, Paz?

280
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:14,933
She's not your friend.

281
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,033
What?

282
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:18,033
Sis, I'm really sorry.

283
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:23,133
But I can't take it anymore
that you're believing fake news.

284
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:27,633
Sis, she's not a good person.
She's not your friend.

285
00:15:27,767 --> 00:15:32,400
I'm sorry, but she's our enemy.

286
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,600
What?

287
00:15:37,033 --> 00:15:37,867
What?

288
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,167
Sis, I'm sorry.

289
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:40,767
Felma.

290
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:42,000
Felma, look at me.

291
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:43,367
Look at me.

292
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,600
Me.

293
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,300
I'm your real bestfriend.

294
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,533
Sis, it's me.

295
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:28,033
Felma, if you only knew...

296
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:32,900
how many nights
I dreamed of doing this to you.

297
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,133
Now...

298
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,333
let's make that dream a reality.

299
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,200
Hazel!

300
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:11,900
Hazel, stop it!

301
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:13,367
Hazel, stop!

302
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,467
Hazel!

303
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,300
Friend!

304
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:17,400
- Friend!
- Stop!

305
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:20,567
Friend, you were dreaming.

306
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:23,400
- Friend.
- Hazel is going to kill me.

307
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:24,767
It was just a nightmare.

308
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,533
Look.

309
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:27,367
Hazel isn't here.

310
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,467
I knew it.

311
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,967
That witch really
does have bad intentions.

312
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:32,400
Friend, I'm sorry.

313
00:17:32,533 --> 00:17:33,300
You must've had that nightmare

314
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:35,833
because of what I told you
earlier.

315
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:38,000
Friend, calm down, okay?

316
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:38,967
Manuel is on his way.

317
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,900
Manuel will watch over you,
all right?

318
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:45,433
Friend?

319
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:49,200
Bro.

320
00:17:57,300 --> 00:18:01,900
I know we already made
peace back in Davao.

321
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:03,600
But...

322
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:06,167
I never really got the chance
to properly thank you

323
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:09,667
for everything you've done
for my family.

324
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:13,967
And I never got to say sorry.

325
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,833
Bro, I'm really sorry.

326
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:18,867
I thought you were my enemy.

327
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,867
My rival.

328
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:25,267
I was jealous of you.

329
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,767
You had every right.

330
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,067
And I understand.

331
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:33,433
If I were in your place,
I'd think the same.

332
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:35,100
Yeah, Bro.

333
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:37,867
But I didn't just think badly
of you.

334
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,233
I went after you more than once.

335
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:42,633
Turns out, I was wrong.

336
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:46,400
You know, Bro, when I heard
what you said to Hazel,

337
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:50,600
my anger disappeared.

338
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:51,667
So did my jealousy.

339
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,667
And I admired you
for who you are.

340
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:57,433
Now I understand
how hard things are for you

341
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,867
and how heavy your situation is.

342
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,567
I'm managing, Manuel.

343
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:04,767
Because I respect you and Felma.

344
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,500
You know what, Bro?

345
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:11,900
You're a good man.

346
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:13,667
Don't ever change.

347
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,667
I won't.

348
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,567
I'll always love Felma...

349
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,667
as a friend.

350
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:20,900
And the kids...

351
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:22,300
as part of my life.

352
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:22,967
No, Bro.

353
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,700
As your own kids.

354
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:27,833
You were the father they needed
when I wasn't there.

355
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,667
That's why I want you
to be their second dad.

356
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:36,833
And I hope we can be friends,
Bro.

357
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,500
Real friends.

358
00:19:41,933 --> 00:19:43,400
- Bro?
- Bro.

359
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:47,600
All right.

360
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:53,867
Come on, Auntie.

361
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,367
We're so careful
about what we tell mom.

362
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:56,733
And then you went
and said everything.

363
00:19:56,867 --> 00:19:57,900
Sorry, my Godson.

364
00:19:58,033 --> 00:19:59,967
I just couldn't stand hearing
her call

365
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:03,233
that goblin her "bestfriend."

366
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,600
- Mom.
- Careful, Mom.

367
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:06,733
Mom, I'll move this a little.

368
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:07,533
Jeff.

369
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:09,200
Okay.

370
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,000
Slowly, Mom.

371
00:20:11,133 --> 00:20:11,867
- Mom.
- Careful with the dextrose.

372
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:12,833
Thank you.

373
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:21,233
Kids, I know
you're just protecting me.

374
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:25,667
And it's actually good
that Paz told me the truth

375
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:28,333
that Hazel
isn't really my friend.

376
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:30,567
Honestly, Mom...

377
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:34,233
I've wanted to tell you
that for a long time.

378
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:39,800
We just worried about how
it might affect your condition.

379
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:44,867
What did Hazel do to me?

380
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:53,767
Hey.

381
00:20:56,267 --> 00:20:59,433
Friend, someone remembered you.

382
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,700
Not just remembered.

383
00:21:10,767 --> 00:21:13,100
It seems like
they're talking about me.

384
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:16,367
Could it be Manuel?

385
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:18,600
Yeah, right. I wish.

386
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,133
It's his kids.

387
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:27,933
His "made in processed meat"
kids.

388
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:29,067
You know...

389
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:35,067
it probably just means
they're uneasy.

390
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,767
And it also means...

391
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,867
I'm a threat to them.
Which is a good thing.

392
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,400
Come on.

393
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:47,133
What did Hazel do to me?

394
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,667
Mom, a lot.

395
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:51,800
Not just to you. To all of us.

396
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:55,333
So she's really that evil?

397
00:21:55,467 --> 00:21:57,667
To the highest level, Mom.

398
00:21:59,667 --> 00:22:01,367
- Mom?
- Sis.

399
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,800
I'm okay.

400
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,067
Let's stop this.

401
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:11,633
Let's not make mom
think about it anymore.

402
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:14,933
Yeah. Let's focus on her
recovery.

403
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:17,533
So, Mom, have you decided?

404
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:26,033
I'm scared, Doctor.

405
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:35,500
If I enter the operating room,
I might not come out alive.

406
00:22:35,633 --> 00:22:40,633
But I'm also scared that
if I don't have the surgery...

407
00:22:40,767 --> 00:22:46,167
I might completely forget
the people I love.

408
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,133
So...

409
00:22:55,967 --> 00:22:57,233
yes, Doctor.

410
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:00,633
I'll go through
with the surgery.

411
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:20,000
So, where would you like
the surgery to be done?

412
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:23,133
Emil highly recommends
this hospital.

413
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:24,567
Then, Doctor...

414
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:25,667
we'll do it here.

415
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,600
What if my memories disappear?

416
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:29,900
What if I forget our children?

417
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:31,033
And you?

418
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:33,367
Listen to your heartbeat.

419
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:35,600
I'm sure your heart
will remember me.

420
00:23:35,733 --> 00:23:38,367
Doctor, please take care of her.

421
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:42,267
I can't promise,
but I'll do my best

422
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:46,333
to remember all of you
when I come out of there.
